27TransformFeedbackMtl::TransformFeedbackMtl(const gl::TransformFeedbackState &state)
28 : TransformFeedbackImpl(state),
29 mBufferHandles{},
30 mBufferOffsets{},
31 mBufferSizes{},
32 mAlignedBufferOffsets{}
33{}
34
35TransformFeedbackMtl::~TransformFeedbackMtl() {}
36
37angle::Result TransformFeedbackMtl::begin(const gl::Context *context,
38 gl::PrimitiveMode primitiveMode)
39{
40 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
41 // Not currently supported with msl compiler
42 if (!contextMtl->getDisplay()->getFeatures().emulateTransformFeedback.enabled)
43 {
44 return angle::Result::Stop;
45 }
46
47 const gl::ProgramExecutable *executable = contextMtl->getState().getProgramExecutable();
48 ASSERT(executable);
49 size_t xfbBufferCount = executable->getTransformFeedbackBufferCount();
50
51 for (size_t bufferIndex = 0; bufferIndex < xfbBufferCount; ++bufferIndex)
52 {
53 const gl::OffsetBindingPointer<gl::Buffer> &binding = mState.getIndexedBuffer(bufferIndex);
54 ASSERT(binding.get());
55
56 BufferMtl *bufferMtl = mtl::GetImpl(binding.get());
57
58 assert(bufferMtl);
59 mBufferOffsets[bufferIndex] = binding.getOffset();
60 mBufferSizes[bufferIndex] = gl::GetBoundBufferAvailableSize(binding);
61 mBufferHandles[bufferIndex] = bufferMtl;
62
63 ASSERT(contextMtl->getDisplay()->getFeatures().emulateTransformFeedback.enabled);
64 const MtlDeviceSize offsetAlignment = mtl::kUniformBufferSettingOffsetMinAlignment;
65
66 // Make sure there's no possible under/overflow with binding size.
67 static_assert(sizeof(MtlDeviceSize) >= sizeof(binding.getSize()),
68 "MtlDeviceSize too small");
69
70 // Set the offset as close as possible to the requested offset while remaining aligned.
71 mAlignedBufferOffsets[bufferIndex] =
72 (mBufferOffsets[bufferIndex] / offsetAlignment) * offsetAlignment;
73 }
74
75 return contextMtl->onBeginTransformFeedback(xfbBufferCount, mBufferHandles);
76}
77
78angle::Result TransformFeedbackMtl::end(const gl::Context *context)
79{
80 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
81 // Not currently supported with msl compiler
82 if (!contextMtl->getDisplay()->getFeatures().emulateTransformFeedback.enabled)
83 {
84 return angle::Result::Stop;
85 }
86
87 // If there's an active transform feedback query, accumulate the primitives drawn.
88 const gl::State &glState = context->getState();
89 gl::Query *transformFeedbackQuery =
90 glState.getActiveQuery(gl::QueryType::TransformFeedbackPrimitivesWritten);
91
92 if (transformFeedbackQuery)
93 {
94 mtl::GetImpl(transformFeedbackQuery)->onTransformFeedbackEnd(mState.getPrimitivesDrawn());
95 }
96 contextMtl->onEndTransformFeedback();
97 return angle::Result::Continue;
98}
99
100angle::Result TransformFeedbackMtl::pause(const gl::Context *context)
101{
102 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
103 return contextMtl->onPauseTransformFeedback();
104}
105
106angle::Result TransformFeedbackMtl::resume(const gl::Context *context)
107{
108 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
109 const gl::ProgramExecutable *executable = contextMtl->getState().getProgramExecutable();
110 ASSERT(executable);
111 size_t xfbBufferCount = executable->getTransformFeedbackBufferCount();
112 return contextMtl->onBeginTransformFeedback(xfbBufferCount, mBufferHandles);
113}
114
115angle::Result TransformFeedbackMtl::bindIndexedBuffer(
116 const gl::Context *context,
117 size_t index,
118 const gl::OffsetBindingPointer<gl::Buffer> &binding)
119{
120 UNIMPLEMENTED();
121
122 return angle::Result::Continue;
123}
124
125void TransformFeedbackMtl::getBufferOffsets(ContextMtl *contextMtl,
126 GLint drawCallFirstVertex,
127 int32_t *offsetsOut,
128 size_t offsetsSize) const
129{
130 if (!contextMtl->getDisplay()->getFeatures().emulateTransformFeedback.enabled)
131 return;
132
133 GLsizeiptr verticesDrawn = mState.getVerticesDrawn();
134 const std::vector<GLsizei> &bufferStrides =
135 mState.getBoundProgram()->getTransformFeedbackStrides();
136 const gl::ProgramExecutable *executable = contextMtl->getState().getProgramExecutable();
137 ASSERT(executable);
138 size_t xfbBufferCount = executable->getTransformFeedbackBufferCount();
139
140 ASSERT(xfbBufferCount > 0);
141
142 // The caller should make sure the offsets array has enough space. The maximum possible
143 // number of outputs is gl::IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFERS.
144 ASSERT(offsetsSize >= xfbBufferCount);
145
146 for (size_t bufferIndex = 0; bufferIndex < xfbBufferCount; ++bufferIndex)
147 {
148 int64_t offsetFromDescriptor =
149 static_cast<int64_t>(mBufferOffsets[bufferIndex] - mAlignedBufferOffsets[bufferIndex]);
150 int64_t drawCallVertexOffset = static_cast<int64_t>(verticesDrawn) - drawCallFirstVertex;
151
152 int64_t writeOffset =
153 (offsetFromDescriptor + drawCallVertexOffset * bufferStrides[bufferIndex]) /
154 static_cast<int64_t>(sizeof(uint32_t));
155
156 offsetsOut[bufferIndex] = static_cast<int32_t>(writeOffset);
157
158 // Assert on overflow. For now, support transform feedback up to 2GB.
159 ASSERT(offsetsOut[bufferIndex] == writeOffset);
160 }
161}
